    <h2>1. Convection Ovens: The Most Popular Choice for Indian Bakeries</h2>
    <p>Convection ovens use a fan to circulate hot air, ensuring even heat distribution. They're the most popular choice for Indian bakeries for several reasons: they're relatively affordable, easy to use, heat up quickly, and produce consistent results across a wide range of products.</p>
    <p>A convection oven excels at pastries, cakes, cookies, rusks, and anything that benefits from even browning. It's not ideal for sourdough or artisan breads that need bottom heat — for those, you'll want a deck oven.</p>

    <h3>Convection Oven Prices in India 2026</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>4-tray countertop (entry-level Indian brands)</strong>: ₹35,000 – ₹55,000</li>
      <li><strong>4-tray countertop (imported/mid-range)</strong>: ₹55,000 – ₹85,000</li>
      <li><strong>6-tray countertop</strong>: ₹65,000 – ₹1,10,000</li>
      <li><strong>8-tray floor model</strong>: ₹85,000 – ₹1,60,000</li>
      <li><strong>10-tray floor model</strong>: ₹1,20,000 – ₹2,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>16-tray floor model (heavy commercial)</strong>: ₹2,00,000 – ₹4,00,000</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Top convection oven brands available in India: Unox (Italy), Rational (Germany), Sinmag (Taiwan), Salva (Spain), Bongard (France), and Indian brands like Genius, Maharaja Whiteline (commercial range), and Ekon.</p>

