    <h2>7. Which Bakery Oven Should You Buy?</h2>
    <p>Here's our recommendation based on common Indian bakery setups:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Starting a small home bakery (budget ₹50,000 – ₹1L):</strong> A 4-6 tray countertop convection oven. Don't overspend on your first oven.</li>
      <li><strong>Opening a neighbourhood bakery (budget ₹1L – ₹3L):</strong> An 8-10 tray floor convection oven plus a 2-deck oven if you bake bread.</li>
      <li><strong>Scaling to medium production (budget ₹3L – ₹8L):</strong> A 3-deck oven for bread and a 10-16 tray convection oven for pastries.</li>
      <li><strong>Commercial bakery (budget ₹8L – ₹20L):</strong> A full-rack rotary oven for volume plus a convection oven for specialty products.</li>
      <li><strong>Industrial bakery (₹20L+):</strong> Multiple rotary rack ovens, potentially with a tunnel oven for continuous production.</li>
    </ul>

